BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313492810@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260312T160927Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T100000
SUMMARY:Sunday Long Run from PRC NW
DESCRIPTION:Portland Running Co. Weekly Group Runs\nPortland Running Company leads a long run every Sunday morning departing from our location at 2258 NW Raleigh St. in Portland.\n\nWe decide the route(s) on the spot\; there is almost always a contingent heading into Forest Park to hit the trails. Other routes we like include Terwilliger/Council Crest\, Mount Tabor\, and the Sellwood Bridge Loop. Distances vary\, but most folks run for about two hours.\n\nIf you've never run with PRC before\, you may need to sign a waiver beforehand. (No dogs\, please.) Free and open to all\, like all of PRC's Group Runs. More info and waiver here: https://portlandrunning.com/pages/weekly-group-runs
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/portland-running-co-weekly-group-runs/events/313492810/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260223T164929Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T164929Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/a/7/7/600_459139063.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313516471@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260312T160927Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260316T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260316T190000
SUMMARY:Monday Night Easy Run in Beaverton
DESCRIPTION:Portland Running Co. Weekly Group Runs\nJessa and Kristin are your leaders for Beaverton's easygoing Monday-night run/walk. All paces and abilities welcome. Weather-permitting\, we'll use the Fanno Creek Trail\, but alternative neighborhood routes are the norm during winter and into spring.\n\nDistances vary\, but usually 3–5 miles. Lights and reflective clothing are recommended. No charge for this run\, like all PRC group runs: https://portlandrunning.com/pages/weekly-group-runs.\n\nAll are welcome\, but no dogs please.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/portland-running-co-weekly-group-runs/events/313516471/
